text: The 1932 Kentucky Wildcats football team was an American football team that represented the University of Kentucky in the Southern Conference (SoCon) during the 1932 college football season. In their sixth season under head coach Harry Gamage, the Wildcats compiled a 4–5 record (4–5 against SoCon opponents), finished 11th in the conference, and outscored opponents by a total of 116 to 77. The team played its home games at McLean Stadium in Lexington, Kentucky. ==Schedule== ==References== Kentucky Category:Kentucky Wildcats football seasons Kentucky Wildcats football
